<section id="AboutTheAuthor">
    <h2>About the Author</h2>
    <div>      
        <p>
            <img id="AboutImage" src="~/Images/Danharmon.jpg" />
            Yo. I'm <strong>Daniel Allred</strong>, the fellow who made this tower. Er.. Maybe "is currently making" is probably more appropriate.
            I'm a happily married, 20-something year old programmer by trade but not by passion. Frankly, I would much prefer to build stuff and make up stories than code,
            but my happiness doesn't pay the bills. Y'all know how it is. I'm addled with physical and mental health problems from DDD(degenerative disk disease) to dyslexia, ADD, 
            and crippling anxiety/depression because <em>I'm a 20-something year old and it's @DateTime.Now.Year, so of course I am.</em>
        </p>
        
        <p>
            I graduated with honors from The University of Southern Mississippi with a degree in Computer Science. The "with honors" bit is nice to say, but it doesn't really
            help with much. I really dragged my feet through high school and before, which is to say I got miserable grades and didn't care about learning. This was a lot to do
            with untreated ADD and dyslexia making me feel inadequate and unwilling to really try for fear of failing. Moving on to college I realized that failure wasn’t anything 
            to be scared of and was even a useful learning tool so long as I didn’t beat myself down over it. With a new lease on my own personal shortcomings, I gave college my best go.
        </p>

        <p>
