            to own our very own business: a hobby shop/ caf&eacute;. 
        </p>

        <p>
            On a personal interest level, I've been Dungeon Mastering since I was about 12, which has been a tremendous journey. I love Tabletop Roleplaying games of all types. 
            I’m big into miniature painting also of all types. Despite being 6.5”, never drinking anything alcoholic, and shaving every other day, my fantasy race identification 
            is still the <em>stout, honorable, and stubborn dwarf.</em>
        </p>

    </div>
</section>


<section id="AboutTheAuthor">
    <h2>What's the deal with this website?</h2>
    <div>
        <p>
            I bought this domain back when I was first looking for work out of college. I thought having a website might help my chances of getting a job, but as luck would have it,
            I got hired a couple days after I got it. That meant that towerofillusion.com just kind of floated around, owned but empty. Lately, my work has been slow and I thought it would
            be fun to try making something for the domain so here we are.
        </p>


        <h3>Illusion Lite</h3>
        <p>
            The name <em>Tower of Illusion</em> comes from a tabletop board game I worked long and hard on some time ago. I wanted a platform to put my work on so that people could see it
            and access the components of the game for free. Like a russian nesting doll of incomplete projects, this also was brushed to the side when I found work. The game, Tower of 
            Illusion, may very well be on an indefinite hiatus, but that doesn't mean it's forgotten. I gutted portions of the game's mechanics to build the tabletop roleplaying system 
            "Tales of Illusion," whose mechanics were further distilled down into "Illusion Lite," which is a simple game system that can be found here! Maybe a little complicated? I 
            probably should have held onto the russian nesting doll comparison for now… But hey! It’s free, and anything you could need to play it is here, so give it a shot if you want 
            something fast paced, simple, and geared toward one night adventures.
        </p>

        <h3>Hobby Blog</h3>
        <p>
            Instagram isn’t really my thing, but I’ve been posting all of my painting there just to have them in one place so when someone asks “what do you do for fun” I can just show 
            them my stuff all in one place. I wanted somewhere more personal to put more details per post, so this seemed like a good fit for that want.
        </p>

    </div>
</section>